\begin{frame}{Hyman Minsky}
There is inherent instability in the system.  The \emph{Financial Instability Hypothesis} (FIH)
\begin{itemize}[<+-| alert@+>]
\item The economy will evolve from one of \emph{hedge financing}
\item To \emph{speculative financing}
\begin{itemize}[<+-| alert@+>]
\item Debt-to-equity ratio rises
\item Repayments are high relative to income
\end{itemize}
\item \emph{Ponzie Finance} where income is insufficient to pay interest or principal 
\end{itemize}
\end{frame}

\begin{frame}{Minsky Moment}
The reversal is brutal
\begin{itemize}[<+-| alert@+>]
\item It is very hard to determine when the bubble will burst
\item The crash is more intense and explosive than the build up of instability
\item Financial institutions are interconnected.  There are non-linear network effects
\end{itemize}
\end{frame}

