\begin{frame}{Sudden Stops}
Krugman and others analysed the process of the Asian crisis.  It also applies to the ERM and elsewhere
\begin{itemize}[<+-| alert@+>]
\item There is some fundamental imbalance or weakness
\item There are speculative attacks on fixed exchange rates
\item \emph{Hedge Funds} Use leverage to increase the size of their bets
\item Crash requires overseas borrowing (to plug the loss of foreign exchange reserves)
\item IMF have imposed austerity measures on the top of collapse of financial system and devaluation of the exchange rate
\end{itemize}
\end{frame}

\begin{frame}{Sudden Stops 2}
This is most frequently associated with fixed exchange rates, a reversal of currency flow and banking crisis
\begin{itemize}[<+-| alert@+>]
\item Positive attitude encourages inflow of capital
\item Wages and asset prices rise
\item Central Bank fights exchange rate appreciation
\item Low interest foreign currency loans increase fragility
\end{itemize}
\end{frame}

