\begin{frame}{Political Economy}
There are a range of views that suggest that economic and financial crisis are a function of political power
\begin{itemize}[<+-| alert@+>]
\item Financialisation of the economy
\begin{itemize}
\item Trading of commodities
\end{itemize}
\item Rising consumer debt is a response to the increase in inequality
\begin{itemize}
\item The only way to maintain consumer spending
\end{itemize}
\item Globalisation of capital has led to a flow of financial capital around the world
\begin{itemize}
\item Evades regulation and tax
\item Causes problems when it arrives and when it leaves
\end{itemize}
\end{itemize}
\end{frame}

\begin{frame}{Larry Summers - bubble land}
Lack of investment requires bubbles
\begin{itemize}[<+-| alert@+>]
\item Real interest rate required to stimulate investment is negative
\begin{itemize}
\item Cyclical caution
\item Lack of monetisable investment opportunities
\end{itemize}
\item Investment must be encouraged by capital gains
\item Capital gains are asset appreciation 
\item Economy lurches from one bubble to the next to encourage sufficient investment to spur the economy
\end{itemize}
\end{frame}

